<P>
NEWS BITES : A SHORT ONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES PERRY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Riedel, which many wine-lovers say makes the best wine glasses around, has 
always specialized: Bordeaux glasses, Burgundy glasses, even a special size and 
shape of glass for Zinfandel. Now it has an everyday glass (somewhat like the 
Zinfandel, actually) for any old wine.The Gourmet Glass (style 416/21) has the 
thin, polished rim of fine glassware, rather than the thick, rolled rim of the 
ordinary stuff, but it's only 6 1/4 inches high, making it easy to put in the 
dishwasher. In department and specialty stores and wine shops; for a list of 
sources, phone (800) 642-1859. Ants: The Ultimate Convenience Food 
</P>
<P>
 In Food Insects Newsletter, naturalist Alfred Wallace explains how to eat 
ants: "They are eaten alive; the insect being held by its head as we hold a 
strawberry by its stalk, and the abdomen being bitten off, the body, wings, and 
legs are thrown down on the floor, where they continue to crawl along." CHARLES 
