<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: TITANS' RICABAL SIGNS FREE-AGENT DEAL WITH DODGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton pitcher Dan Ricabal, who was not picked in the amateur 
draft, has signed a free-agent contract with the Dodgers and has been assigned 
to the team's Yakima, Wash., rookie league team. 
</P>
<P>
 Ricabal finished his senior season with a 12-1 record and a 2.84 earned-run 
average after a troubled early season in which he walked 23 batters in 27 1/3 
innings. Ricabal was the winning pitcher in two games in the College World 
Series and in two in the NCAA Midwest I regional. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Dave Harrison, a 6-foot-7 forward for Mt. Hood College in Gresham, Ore., has 
signed a letter of intent to play basketball for Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Harrison averaged 19.5 points and 13.6 rebounds for a team that was 18-11. 
</P>
<P>
 "I think he has an opportunity to be a real good player for Fullerton," said 
Fred Schnell, his coach. "He has good quickness, is very athletic and loves the 
up-tempo game." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Carrie Vaughn, a former captain of the Cypress girls' tennis team, has been 
hired as the school's boys' tennis coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Vaughn, who will graduate from Cal Poly San Luis Obispo this summer, replaces 
Ken Nakama, who was the coach for two seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jamie McCance has been hired as the Servite golf coach. McCance, a teaching 
golf professional at Fullerton Golf Course, takes over for John Ebbe, who 
resigned after coaching for two years. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Four women's soccer players with local ties have signed letters of intent to 
play for Southern California College. 
</P>
<P>
 The school's recruiting class includes Staci Bumstead, Dawn Chastain, Meggan 
Fleener and Jamie Gardiner. Bumstead, a sophomore defender-midfielder, is 
transferring from Cypress College and is also a graduate of Esperanza High. 
</P>
<P>
 Chastain (Esperanza) and Fleener (Newport Harbor), midfielders, will be 
freshmen. Gardiner, a forward, is a 1993 graduate of Sunny Hills. She is 
transferring from Houghton College in New York. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Tina Daly, a left-side hitter from Edison, signed a letter of intent with 
Indiana State, Edison girls' volleyball Coach Dave Mohs said. Daly, an 
All-Sunset League selection, helped Edison finish third in the Sunset League 
and advance to the Southern Section Division II quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Four county high school football players have been selected to play in the 
Southern California Catholic All-Star Football Classic, scheduled at 7 p.m. 
Saturday at Cerritos Gahr High. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei, runner-up in Southern Section Division I, received invitations for 
three of its players. Defensive lineman Brandon Gamboa (5-11, 230 pounds), 
linebacker Jason Rivera (5-9, 207) and tight end-linebacker Pete Silvey (6-3, 
225) join defensive lineman Jim Ahern (6-1, 230) of Servite in representing the 
county. 
</P>
</TEXT>
