<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENCINO GOLFER SHOOTS A 71 IN JUNIOR EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ben Cherney of Encino fired a second-round 71 Wednesday to lead the 
four-player California-Oregon team into fourth place with one round remaining 
in the American Junior Golf Assn. Northern Telecom Tournament at Brentwood 
Country Club in Nashville, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
 Cherney, who will be a senior next fall at Brentwood High, shot a 79 in the 
opening round of the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 In another tournament, Greg Bell of Studio City earned a berth in the 95th 
Southern California Golf Assn. amateur championship by firing a one-over-par 73 
at Lake San Marcos Golf Course. 
</P>
<P>
 Bell was one of 10 players in a field of 64 to advance to the SCGA Amateur, to 
be held July 22-24 at Hacienda Golf Club in La Habra Heights. 
</P>
