<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; STREET ART: FIRST-EVER VENICE SERVICE AWARD GOES TO CARICATURE ARTIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Venice Beach Boardwalk Assn. has awarded caricature artist Walt Davis its 
first-ever Entertainers and Artist Community Service Award. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis, who regularly draws caricatures for boardwalk visitors, received the 
award last week for his years of participation in boardwalk improvement 
projects. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis will receive gift certificates and free meals from merchants valued at 
more than $200. 
</P>
<P>
 The Venice Boardwalk Assn. is an organization of merchants, property owners 
and residents along Oceanfront Walk. The award is intended to recognize 
artists' talents as well as their contributions to the community. 
</P>
</TEXT>
