<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; CRIME: FILM SERIES TO HONOR SLAIN STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At the school attended by two students who were slain early this year in a 
carjacking, plans are under way to make sure the 19-year-olds are always 
remembered. 
</P>
<P>
 Go Matsuura and Takuma Ito were fans and students of film, so Marymount 
College is trying to establish an endowment fund to create the Ito/Matsuura 
Film Series. 
</P>
<P>
 It hopes the event will become an annual film and lecture series featuring the 
work of American directors. 
</P>
<P>
 "After the funeral services, I met with their parents (from Japan) and all 
members of their families and we talked about ways to remember them," college 
President Thomas McFadden said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We discussed many ideas, and I suggested a series on Japanese films, but they 
said no, they liked American films." The school is trying to raise $20,000 to 
$30,000 to fund the film festival.  
</P>
<P>
 Matsuura and Ito were slain in a San Pedro carjacking on March 25. 
</P>
<P>
 Donations can be made to the Ito/Matsuura Film Series, Marymount College, 
30800 Palos Verdes Drive East, Rancho Palos Verdes 90274. Information: (310) 
377-5501. 
