<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PALOS VERDES PENINSULA; MTA TO CONTINUE FUNDS FOR DIAL-A-RIDE 
BUSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Metropolitan Transportation Authority will continue to fund dial-a-ride 
bus service on the Palos Verdes Peninsula and in six other Los Angeles County 
areas over the next fiscal year. 
</P>
<P>
 County Supervisor Deane Dana said the services, which are used by the disabled 
and the elderly, will receive $417,000 in 1994-95. 
</P>
<P>
 The county has pledged $90,000 to the Palos Verdes Peninsula Transit 
Authority, but restrictions have been imposed: Peninsula users will be 
restricted to 32 vouchers per month, with special consideration in some cases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
