<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUT AND ABOUT / KCRW AUCTION: GARDEN PARTY ON A FINE 'SUMMERDAY' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA V. GODBEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A trip to the Bushmills Distilleries in Ireland, a Napa Valley wine-tasting 
weekend and a cooking class at the California Culinary Institute are among the 
items to be auctioned Sunday during the KCRW Foundation's fourth annual 
"Summerday and International Wine, Dine and Travel Auction." 
</P>
<P>
 Things get started at noon when auctioneer Joe Smith takes the stage at the 
Pacific Design Center in West Hollywood. Smith, an avid wine collector, will 
direct the bidding on 130 unique travel packages, wine collections and events. 
</P>
<P>
 After the bidding, tasting begins in the "Garden of Earthly Delights." Guests 
will feast on an array of cuisine prepared by chefs from nearly three dozen 
Southern California restaurants, including Angeli Caffe's famous pasta and 
Zabie's Caesar salad. 
</P>
<P>
 Celebrated winemakers, distillers and brewers from around the world will then 
offer unlimited tastings of their creations. Nonalcoholic beverages will also 
be served. KCRW music personalities will spin the tunes of yesteryear and 
today. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is a chance to gain insight into the working habits, methods and 
inspirations of some of the world's top winemakers and chefs. 
</P>
<P>
 Four years ago, Ruth Seymour, station manager at Santa Monica-based KCRW, came 
up with the theme for Summerday. Thinking of Impressionist artist Claude-Oscar 
Monet, she wanted to create an event that replicated the feeling portrayed in 
his garden paintings. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our feeling is (the event should be as) refreshing as one of Monet's gardens. 
. . . He had a real lust for life, cooking and wine," said Lauren Deutsch, 
KCRW's community events producer. "It's really the one time KCRW gets to 
celebrate itself." 
</P>
<P>
 The event is an important fund-raiser for the nonprofit station, an affiliate 
of National Public Radio. Proceeds from this year's event benefit the station's 
new performing arts studio. 
</P>
<P>
 The $75 admission includes the bidder's brunch reception, which begins at 11 
a.m., followed by the noon auction. For tasting only, tickets are $55. 
</P>
<P>
 KCRW Foundation's "Summerday" will be from 11 a.m. to 6 p.m at the Pacific 
Design Center, 8687 Melrose Ave., West Hollywood. Reservations are required. 
Tickets are $75 and $55 and includes parking. No tickets will be sold the day 
of the event. For reservations, call (310) 450-5183. CHRISTINA V. GODBEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
