<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: BRADBURY; EX-OFFICIAL 
WHO MISUSED FUNDS PAYS CITY $110,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Bradbury City Manager Aurora (Dolly) Vollaire paid a settlement of 
$110,000 to the city Tuesday, concluding a civil suit that alleged she 
embezzled $84,000 by using the municipal credit card and other city accounts to 
buy personal luxuries. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have recovered our losses with interest," Bradbury Mayor Bea 
LaPisto-Kirtley said. 
</P>
<P>
 Vollaire was fired last spring from the post she had held for two decades 
after allegations of misspending. A Times investigation showed that Vollaire 
had used city money to buy such items as personal crystal and china, designer 
sunglasses and shoes. The city sued Vollaire in November, 1993, seeking to 
recover the money. 
</P>
<P>
 Vollaire pleaded no contest in April to felony counts of misusing public funds 
and presenting fraudulent claims to the city. She agreed to pay $54,000 
restitution to Bradbury, which is included in the civil settlement. She faces a 
sentencing hearing July 8 on the criminal case. 
</P>
<P>
 The civil settlement, reached Monday, saves the city the cost and time of a 
trial, which could have taken a year to conclude, Bradbury's attorney Wesley 
Beverlin said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
