<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHINA, BRITAIN TO HOLD TALKS ON HONG KONG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Heralding a truce in their 20-month quarrel over Hong Kong's political future, 
Britain and China will hold long-awaited talks next week on the colony's 
transition to Chinese rule. 
</P>
<P>
 An official announcement Wednesday said that the Joint Liaison Group, which 
oversees the mechanics of the 1997 Chinese takeover, will meet in Hong Kong 
from Tuesday through Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061694-0175 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 051812 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
June 16, 1994, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
