<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; MAN GETS 6 YEARS IN FATAL STABBING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A judge has sentenced an Oxnard man who admitted killing his ex-girlfriend's 
son during a Christmas Day stabbing to six years in state prison. 
</P>
<P>
 The sentence handed down Tuesday by Ventura County Superior Court Judge 
Lawrence Storch was part of a plea agreement reached between lawyers for 
defendant Jose Jimenez and the district attorney's office. 
</P>
<P>
 Prosecutors charged Jimenez with murder for the fatal stabbing of Isaias 
Guerrero Morales, 21. The victim was knifed in the yard of his family's 
Campbell Way home. 
</P>
<P>
 But a jury last month acquitted the defendant of murder after the defense 
argued that Jimenez acted to ward off an attack by Guerrero. 
</P>
<P>
 Prosecutors then agreed to accept Jimenez's plea to voluntary manslaughter 
after the jury could not reach a verdict on a charge of involuntary 
manslaughter. Part of that agreement called for the defendant to be sentenced 
to the six-year term instead of the 12-year sentence he could have received. 
DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
