By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Investors hoping to run a restaurant at the end of the Ventura Pier should 
have 2 1/2 weeks to submit a proposal to Ventura City Hall, a council committee 
recommended Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Less than a month after negotiations fell through with Seattle businessman Hal 
Griffith -- the council's original choice to operate the restaurant -- the city 
already has offers from two local restaurateurs. 
</P>
<P>
 Both Eric Wachter, owner of Eric Ericsson's Fish Co. restaurant, and Sandy 
Smith, owner of Rosarita Beach Cafe, say they want to compete for a chance to 
build a seafood restaurant on the wooden pier. 
</P>
<P>
 "If you are looking at fast-tracking this, it wouldn't take me too long to put 
some (plans) together," Smith told the council committee. 
</P>
<P>
 City staff told council members that if they didn't quickly pick someone 
local, the restaurant might not open until the summer of 1996, instead of next 
summer as originally planned. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council will discuss the issue at its Monday night meeting. Committee 
members said they will recommend setting the bid deadline for the first full 
week in July. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
