By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Oxnard man pleaded guilty Wednesday to murder and use of a deadly weapon in 
connection with the April stabbing death of his sister's 19-year-old boyfriend. 
</P>
<P>
 Donald Culbertson, 24, also entered guilty pleas to two counts of aggravated 
assault that stem from separate attacks on his former girlfriend and another 
woman. 
</P>
<P>
 Culbertson faces 21 years to life in prison, said Deputy Dist. Atty. Donald C. 
Glynn. Glynn said Culbertson's plea would lead to conviction of second-degree 
murder at sentencing. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's got an aggressive, violent personality where he beats up women," Glynn 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested Culbertson in connection with the slaying of David Rubio of 
Oxnard on April 10. Rubio was stabbed in an alley behind the 5200 block of 
Columbus Place. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim had borrowed a car from Culbertson's sister and was late returning 
it one night, Glynn said. That led to an argument and Rubio's death, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Glynn also said Culbertson badly beat his ex-girlfriend, Mysti Giralde, 20, 
damaging her pancreas. The second assault charge stemmed from an attack against 
the girlfriend of Culbertson's stepfather, he said. DWAYNE BRAY 
