<HEADLINE>
<P>
3-YEAR-OLD BOY WOUNDED BY GUNFIRE AT MOTEL IN VENTURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 3-year-old boy was shot in the back Wednesday at a Ventura motel where he 
was staying with his mother, brother and another man, Ventura police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A police dispatcher said investigators had determined that the shooting was an 
accident.It was not known who fired the shot.  
</P>
<P>
 The victim, David Cook, was in critical condition after surgery late Wednesday 
in the intensive-care unit at Ventura County Medical Center, a nursing 
supervisor said. The boy's 6-year-old brother, Keith, was also taken to the 
hospital but was released after unspecified treatment, the supervisor said. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred about 5 p.m. at the Silver Sands Motel and Apartments, 
3215 E. Main St., according to the dispatcher. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents said they heard a single shot and then a woman's scream before the 
mother of the injured boy emerged from Room 4 with the bleeding toddler in her 
arms. 
</P>
<P>
 "We heard a shot and just got one of those feelings like, oh my God!" said 
Aura Hennig, who was staying in a room across the parking lot of the motel. "We 
looked out the window and heard her scream. She was holding the baby. She was 
really panicked and upset." 
</P>
<P>
 Hennig and her husband, Hans, ran over to help. 
</P>
<P>
 "The baby was crying all the way through it," Aura Hennig said. "His whole 
back was blown off, more or less." 
</P>
<P>
 Motel manager Max Wang said the mother had occupied the room since April, 
along with her sons and a man whom Wang described as a family friend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
