<P>
 Sony Unveils Chip for Video Game Machine: Sony Computer Entertainment, a unit 
of Sony Corp., and LSI Logic Corp. unveiled an advanced chip that will power 
Sony's new video game player, the PlayStation.The PlayStation microchip 
contains advanced three-dimensional geometric graphics and high-resolution 
full-motion video. It is a 32-bit RISC (reduced instruction set computing) 
chip, which has architecture that reduces the complexity of the chip by using 
simpler instructions. The PlayStation, announced in May, is a CD-based home 
video game player. It will not be available in the United States until sometime 
next year. It will be shipped in Japan at the end of 1994. Sony said it expects 
the system to be priced at about $500. 
