<TEXT>
<P>
 China Cracks Down on Futures Industry: The government announced a sweeping 
crackdown on the nascent industry that will stop trading on most of the 
country's 40-odd exchanges and prevent brokerages from placing orders overseas. 
The move follows a warning by the official People's Daily newspaper Sunday that 
speculation on international futures markets had led to huge foreign exchange 
losses. Most futures exchanges will be turned into wholesale markets that will 
be banned from dealing in futures. 
</P>
