<P>
 * Gerald T. Devlin, vice president of sales for the Americas for AST Research 
Inc., has resigned. Devlin, who has been with the Irvine personal computer 
manufacturer since January, 1993, is leaving to become vice president of 
worldwide sales for the Desktop Document division of Xerox Corp. A successor 
for Devlin has not yet been chosen. 
</P>
<P>
 * Victor L. Prechtl has been appointed vice president and controller of Fluor 
Corp., an Irvine engineering, construction, maintenance and technical services 
company. He was previously executive director of internal audit. Prechtl joined 
Fluor in 1981 and held various positions in corporate accounting before 
becoming executive director of internal audit in 1991. Succeeding him will be 
Dennis Hart, who has been appointed senior director of internal audit. 
</P>
<P>
 * Steve Grote has been appointed president of Brinderson Constructors in 
Irvine, which provides construction services to the refining and process plant 
industries. Before joining the company, Grote was president of Brown & Root 
Braun, with responsibility for petroleum and chemical engineering and 
construction.  
</P>
<P>
 * Ara Sagerian has been elected to the board of Satellite Technology 
Management Inc. in Costa Mesa, bringing the number of directors to six. 
Sagerian is president of RF Microsystems Inc. in San Diego, which was acquired 
by Satellite Technology in December. Satellite Technology is a manufacturer of 
satellite and radio communications products. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jennifer Lund has been appointed vice president of creative services for 
CMA/West, an Irvine advertising agency. She was formerly creative director.  
</P>
<P>
 * Jeff Bingham has joined the Santa Ana environmental engineering firm of CH2M 
Hill as manager of transportation and environmental planning for the Southern 
California region. He previously managed the environmental services group for 
Parsons Brinckerhoff's Pacific Southwest region. Before that, Bingham was with 
Caltrans for 10 years, most recently as chief of environmental planning in the 
Los Angeles district. 
</P>
<P>
 * Martin A. Klein III has been appointed by Gov. Pete Wilson to the Advisory 
Council on Economic Development, which promotes California to businesses and 
community organizations across the nation. Klein is first vice president of 
investments for Prudential Securities' Newport Beach office. 
</P>
<P>
 * Rand Bleimeister has been appointed to the newly created position of senior 
vice president, sales and marketing for Virgin Interactive Entertainment's 
North American operations. Before joining the Irvine-based company, he was 
senior vice president for special interest and interactive programming at 
Columbia TriStar's home video operation. Before that, Bleimeister held 
executive positions with Nelson Entertainment, Embassy Home Video, Capitol/EMI 
Music and Warner Brothers. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jack Schember has been promoted to publisher of ResponseTV magazine in Santa 
Ana. He was previously associate publisher. Schember joined the publication in 
1992 as editor and became associate publisher and editor-in-chief last year. 
</P>
