<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIDBITS, TIPS AND A LITTLE TRIVIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A well-tied tie is the first serious step in life. -- Oscar Wilde 
</P>
<P>
 Who Buys Ties: About 60% to 65% of ties are purchased by women, according to 
the Neckwear Assn. of America. 
</P>
<P>
 Tie Trivia: Silk represents more than 40% of the market. Polyester, wools and 
wool blends are common. Acetate, rayon, nylon, cotton, linen and ramie are 
sometimes used. 
</P>
<P>
 To pamper your tie:  
</P>
<P>
 * Always hang it up after use to remove wrinkles. The exception: knit ties, 
which should be rolled up and stored in a drawer to prevent stretching. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dry clean it once a year, or as needed for staining. Make sure the dry 
cleaner has the special equipment needed for ties. 
</P>
<P>
 * If you get a spill on a silk tie, don't try to rub it out with water or soda 
water. Just blot with a damp paper or cloth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
