ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; NEW PRINCIPAL HIRED BY HEBREW ACADEMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Hebrew Academy has hired Barry Ziff, a 27-year veteran of education who 
has taught in the Montebello, South Pasadena and Los Angeles unified school 
districts, as its new principal. 
</P>
<P>
 Ziff, who has also spoken at state and international conferences, authored the 
book for parents "Your Challenge, Their Life." 
</P>
<P>
 He will run the nursery-through-12th-grade Hebrew and English program at the 
academy, succeeding Barbara Heneghan. 
