<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; SUSPECT LEADS CHASE THROUGH SEVEN CITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A score of police officers in patrol cars and on motorcycles chased an auto 
theft suspect through seven Orange County cities Wednesday before arresting him 
in Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 Gregory Scott Sullivan, 27, of Tustin was being held without bail in the 
Anaheim City Jail on suspicion of auto theft, possession of stolen property and 
evading officers, Sgt. Kennet G. Brott said. 
</P>
<P>
 The chase began just after noon in a shopping center at Lincoln Avenue and 
Beach Boulevard in Anaheim, police said. An officer noticed that the passenger 
window of a parked pickup truck was smashed, checked the vehicle's license 
plate through a computer, and it came back as stolen, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 When Sullivan returned to the truck, he refused to pull over, Brott said, "and 
off we went." 
</P>
<P>
 The chase, involving officers from various jurisdictions, proceeded through 
areas of Buena Park, Cypress, Fullerton, Brea, Yorba Linda, back to Anaheim and 
finally to Orange, Brott said. There were no collisions or injuries, and 
Sullivan was taken into custody without incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
