<HEADLINE>
<P>
BALLET SELECTS CHOREOGRAPHERS FOR JULY PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS PASLES, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ballet Pacifica has announced the four choreographers who will create works 
for the company during its fourth annual "Pacifica Choreographic Project," 
which runs July 17-30. Rebecca Kelly, Pascal Rioult and David Allan, all of New 
York City, and Paul Vasterling of Nashville, were selected from a pool of 25 
applicants by Molly Lynch, the troupe's artistic director. 
</P>
<P>
 Kelly has danced with Lar Lubovitch and the Charles Weidman Theatre Dance 
Ensemble and has her own company. Rioult, a native of Caen, France, has been a 
member of the Martha Graham Dance Company since 1986. Allan danced with the 
National Ballet of Canada from 1977 to 1988 and has created more than 35 
ballets, eight of which were commissioned by Erik Bruhn for the Canadian 
company. Vasterling has danced in the Ohio Ballet, Ballet Austin, Ballet 
Mississippi, Ballet San Antonio and, most recently, the Nashville Ballet. He 
also has participated in the Carlisle Project, a choreographic workshop in 
Pennsylvania. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ballet Pacifica project will culminate in a performance of the new works 
at South Coast Repertory in Costa Mesa on July 30. Information: (714) 642-9275. 
</P>
</TEXT>
